purpose: The email is a call for papers and workshop/tutorial proposals for the 33rd IEEE International Conference on Software Analysis, Evolution, and Reengineering (SANER 2026), scheduled for March 17-20, 2026, in Limassol, Cyprus. It invites high-quality submissions of original and unpublished research results in various topics related to software analysis, evolution, and reengineering. The email outlines submission instructions, important deadlines, and evaluation criteria for both papers and workshops/tutorials. Additionally, it mentions a special journal issue for selected papers and provides details about the organizing committee.
